Dear gurus, It may be a childish to ask such=
 a question. 
[Kannan:]
It is always good to be a child. Asking question is=
 not childish. It is child-like. A child is ruled by Mercury or Budha, so c=
uriosity, asking questions are a part of a child. And child is the most wis=
e person. A child is the best learner. The whole tragedy of life is that on=
e loses this child as one matures. What one fails to realize is that maturi=
ty is good only in head, not in heart. The heart prefers to stay child-like=
. And that is why all knowledge is received in heart and not in head.

[Bal=
u Mtech [mtechbalu@...] Fri 5/2/2014 15:45: ]
It may be personal, off=
icial or health problems. Some people may suggest to do some poojas, Homams=
, how to overcome the problems of life? Is kaliyuga like that only? When ou=
r problems ll end? What might be the reason for this misery? When the whole=
 world become spiritual base? When do we find joyous people?
[Kannan:] 
The=
 whole problem apparent, seemingly insurmountable and torturous, is a perce=
ptional error. What I mean is that an event appears as a problem because on=
e wishes to see it as a problem. This needs explanation. I can say that thi=
s negative perception or pessimism is due to lack of faith and love. Pessim=
ism forces us to shift our focus away from our kartavyam(righteous action t=
o be undertaken at a given moment and place). To engage consistently in kar=
tavyam requires faith and love. Karmanyevaadhikaarastey Maafaleyshukadhaach=
ana=E2=80=A6..This beautiful verse from ShrimadhBhagavathGeetopanishadam pr=
ecisely tells one to be optimistic and focus on kartavyam.

I share one sec=
ret. The events in one=E2=80=99s life come not to destroy but to bless; rat=
her they come to lift one upwards. They are an opportunity for growth. This=
 is true. But then how it appears torturous for one? Because of lack of fai=
th and love, one becomes pessimistic, and in the process one becomes one=E2=
=80=99s own destroyer and one=E2=80=99s own enemy. The same event which can=
 be used as an opportunity for growth by optimism, becomes the reason for o=
ne=E2=80=99s destruction, due to pessimism. But the funny part of the game =
is that one tend to blame events, destiny, fate, people, kaliyuga, God, wor=
ld etc etc etc and everything else, other than one=E2=80=99s own thinking. =
What a pity!

To understand what optimism is, one can review an event in Ma=
habharata when Pandavas were given a rotting piece of land called Khaandava=
Prastha, which they converted into IndraPrashtha, meaning a heaven like tha=
t of Shri Indra on Earth. But how could they do this miracle? They could ha=
ve very well be pessimistic cursing their fate that they got such a useless=
, rotting, barren land. They did this miracle because our Beloved Shri Krus=
hna was with them. Oh people! When will you realize that taking refuge in N=
aaraayana=E2=80=99s Holy Feet is the nectar of the life! In other words, on=
e suffers because one forgot God. Bring God back into one=E2=80=99s heart, =
and see how life changes for good. God is like a Light. What will happen if=
 one switches off all lights? Darkness? Suffering? Ignorance? Confusion? Wh=
o is Guru? One who removes this darkness and brings back the light. But who=
 can do this? The Grace of God. The Grace and Compassion of God is called G=
uru. This entire concept is packed very nicely into a mantra by Shri Ramali=
nga Vallalar, and it goes thus- Arut-Perum-Jyoti Arut-Perum-Jyoti Thani-Per=
um-Karunai Arut-Perum-Jyoti.

I hope this gives enough inputs to ponder and=
 re-orient towards truth. Thank you.

